The 7th Infantry Division, also known as the Golden Arrow (after its formation sign) and Peshawar Division, (after its garrison city) is the Pakistan Armys oldest and most battle-hardened division.
The Division first saw action during the Indo-Pakistan War of 1948, where it fought and captured some territory in the Poonch sector.
In 1999 during the Kargil War, the division was sent as a reinforcement to the Gultari area.
